Race.SpecificTitle: Chief of Police -- Town of Newellton
Gravity Drainage Dist. No. 3 Prop. No. 1 of 2 -- 2.31 Mills Continuation - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Gravity Drainage District No. 3 Proposition No. 1 of 2
(Millage Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall Gravity Drainage District No. 3 of Tensas Parish, Louisiana (the "District"), continue to levy a two and thirty-one hundredths (2.31) mills tax on all property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $24,400 expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years beginning with the year 2024 and ending with the year 2033, the proceeds of said tax to be used for maintaining drainage work of the District, said millage to represent a ten hundredths of a mill (.10) increase (due to reappraisal) over the 2.21 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2023 pursuant to an election held on May 4, 2013?

Race.SpecificTitle: Gravity Drainage Dist. No. 3 Prop. No. 2 of 2 -- 1.63 Mills Continuation - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Gravity Drainage District No. 3 Proposition No. 2 of 2
(Millage Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall Gravity Drainage District No. 3 of Tensas Parish, Louisiana (the "District"), continue to levy a one and sixty-three hundredths (1.63) mills tax on all property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $17,200 expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years beginning with the year 2024 and ending with the year 2033, the proceeds of said tax to be used for maintaining drainage work of the District, said millage to represent a seven hundredths of a mill (.07) increase (due to reappraisal) over the 1.56 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2023 pursuant to an election held on May 4, 2013?
